---
// InfrastructureBlock.astro
---

<section id="infrastructure" class="py-24 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full border-t border-backend-border">
  <div class="mb-12 text-center md:text-left">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-sans font-bold text-backend-text mb-4">Infrastructure & DevOps</h2>
    <p class="text-backend-muted text-lg font-light">
      Deploying code is only half the battle. Maintaining, scaling, and monitoring the infrastructure is where true reliability is built.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    {/* Block 1 */}
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 md:gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 text-backend-text font-mono text-sm pt-1">
        01 / Containerization
      </div>
      <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Docker & Kubernetes</h3>
        <p class="text-backend-muted leading-relaxed text-sm md:text-base">
          Every service is isolated, reproducible, and scalable. By packaging applications into containers, we eliminate the "it works on my machine" paradigm and ensure environments are identical from local development to production clusters.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full h-px bg-backend-border"></div>

    {/* Block 2 */}
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 md:gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 text-backend-text font-mono text-sm pt-1">
        02 / CI/CD Pipelines
      </div>
      <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Automated Delivery</h3>
        <p class="text-backend-muted leading-relaxed text-sm md:text-base">
          Code must be tested, linted, and built automatically before it ever reaches a server. Robust GitHub Actions workflows ensure that main branch integrations are seamless and zero-downtime deployments are the standard.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full h-px bg-backend-border"></div>

    {/* Block 3 */}
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 md:gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 text-backend-text font-mono text-sm pt-1">
        03 / Observability
      </div>
      <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Monitoring & Logs</h3>
        <p class="text-backend-muted leading-relaxed text-sm md:text-base">
          You cannot fix what you cannot see. Centralized logging, distributed tracing, and real-time metrics dashboards allow for proactive bottleneck identification before users ever experience latency.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
